summary:
Marvel Characters as Things Me/My Friends have said
Natasha: I ran in heels before I walked in them
Bucky: I really need a hair...
body:
Marvel Characters as Things Me/My Friends have said

Natasha: I ran in heels before I walked in them

Bucky: I really need a hair cut there’s hair everywhere

Steve: [wearing an American flag themed t-shirt, pants, and shades with red, white, and blue ducktape in random places and stars & stripes face paint] If I don’t win this patriotism contest so help me..

Sam: You know how some kids when they were little jumped off furniture & pretended to fly? That’s still me now

Stephen: There’s so much stupid in the room, I need my crystals to ward off the bad energy

Wanda: I got so mad when my friends were ignoring me for hours on end that I finally snapped and just uppercut one of them in the stomach

Peter Parker: So if a revolution is a 360° turn then successful societal Revolutions are essentially only half-Revolutions and when you refer to a Revolution being only half-successful that’s half of the half meaning half of 180 meaning 90° meaning it’s a quarter-Revolution

Tony: i’ll talk to someone abt my problems the day i can list them all

title: Spider-Man Revealed
body:
read it on the AO3 at https://ift.tt/2PjsIi2

by denyingmyselfalways

“Do you think he’ll be enough?”

Peter didn’t have to strain too much to listen. He could hear the city just outside, so he must be in a room on the perimeter of whatever building they were in. The man he’d just heard speak couldn’t be more than ten feet away from him. He shifted slightly, testing his bonds. Just rope around his ankles and wrists. Amateurs. A pillowcase was covering his head, so he cracked open his eyes.

“I told you already, Tony’s practically this kid’s dad. He’ll be enough.”

Confusion jabbed at Peter’s brain. Practically his dad? Who got that impression? At least they didn’t seem to know he was Spider-man. For now, anyway.

“I don’t know, Chadwick, this Parker kid doesn’t really seem Stark’s style.”

“Since when did Tony Stark ever make much sense? Now, do you remember the plan?” Chadwick snapped at his companion.

“Yeah, yeah. Wait for Stark to show up, threaten the kid, shoot Tony, get the hell out of here,” the nameless man seemed bored saying it.

Confusion jabbed at Peter’s brain. Practically his dad? Who got that impression? At least they didn’t seem to know he was Spider-man. For now, anyway.

“I don’t know, Chadwick, this Parker kid doesn’t really seem Stark’s style.”

“Since when did Tony Stark ever make much sense? Now, do you remember the plan?” Chadwick snapped at his companion.

“Yeah, yeah. Wait for Stark to show up, threaten the kid, shoot Tony, get the hell out of here,” the nameless man seemed bored saying it.
